text.tspan: Various Aspects of the Inner Life — The Growth in Life
All of God’s riches compressed into this seed,
Equally precious faith, will meet our need;
God’s divine energy, virtue from within,
Supplies the way to make us just like Him.
Virtue brings knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ,
God’s divine power, and Christ to be our life;
And, with all diligence, His life we will absorb,
While rooted, grounded in God’s Holy Word.
Self-control, dwells in the structure of the tree,
Self kept in check, from our spirit is set free;
Life now can flow and our passions and our lust
Will be restrained, for this in God we trust.
Christ our endurance will branch, increase, and grow;
Passing though hardship, Christ’s sufferings we know;
Our daily living with spirit exercised,
Expresses God to be our kingdom prize.
Godliness thrives in a garden of God’s love,
Brotherly love with a source from heav’n above,
Love so delightful, love steadfast, strong and pure.
A blooming love, a love that will endure.
Ultimate love is the sweet, eternal fruit,
God, as true love, through the branch, the trunk, and root;
Nobler and higher, such love we now shall be
